  "prompt": "Can I make a voice call from my iPad using Jio SIM?",
  "response": "Yes, you can make voice calls from your iPad using a Jio SIM, but it requires certain conditions. Here are the general methods:\n\n1. **iPad Cellular Model**: Ensure you have an iPad model that supports cellular connectivity. You'll need to insert your Jio SIM into the iPad.\n\n2. **Using Jio Network**: Once the SIM is inserted, you can make voice calls using various applications like WhatsApp, FaceTime, or any other VoIP service. However, traditional voice calling (like on a smartphone) may not be directly supported on iPads.\n\n3. **Wi-Fi Calling**: If your Jio plan supports Wi-Fi calling, you might be able to use that feature if you\u2019re connected to a Wi-Fi network.\n\n4. **JioCall App**: Jio offers a specific app called JioCall that allows you to make voice calls over the Jio network. You can download it from the App Store and set it up to use your Jio number for calls.\n\n5. **Using Continuity Features**: If you have an iPhone and an iPad both using the same Apple ID, you can use the \"Calls on Other Devices\" feature to make and receive calls on your iPad.\n\nKeep in mind that regular cellular voice calling (like on a phone) is not typically supported on iPads, and you would need to rely on apps or services that use data for voice communication.",
